                                                  written lines: 43; Uniform layout. Visible pricking and horizontal ruling in ink, page by page, and vertical ruling with plummet, also page by page. Hair side and flesh side of the folios distinguishable.Last line written within ruling.Initial words in larger square script. Catchword at the end of each quire.Contains marginal annotations.  Many censorial erasures, e.g., folio 41v, 55r, 58v, 146r, etc.Marginal drawings, e.g., folio 86v, 87v.
